"use strict";(self.webpackChunkta_web=self.webpackChunkta_web||[]).push([[3278],{7641:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"let\'s-go-exploring","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/let\'s-go-exploring","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-06-28-new.md","title":"Let\'s Go Exploring!","description":"Let\'s Go Exploring!","date":"2022-06-28T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 28, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":0.025,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"let\'s-go-exploring","title":"Let\'s Go Exploring!"},"nextItem":{"title":"What is it? I don\u2019t know.","permalink":"/pnotions/i-don\'t-know"}},"content":"![Let\'s Go Exploring!](../static/img/idontknow.jpg)\\n\\n[Prashanthi \ud83d\udc7e](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/)"},{"id":"i-don\'t-know","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/i-don\'t-know","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-06-26-I_dont_know.md","title":"What is it? I don\u2019t know.","description":"Still don\u2019t know","date":"2022-06-26T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 26, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":0.94,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"i-don\'t-know","title":"What is it? I don\u2019t know."},"prevItem":{"title":"Let\'s Go Exploring!","permalink":"/pnotions/let\'s-go-exploring"},"nextItem":{"title":"8 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/8notions"}},"content":"Still don\u2019t know\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nYou are probably wondering how I cannot know what I am writing. Well, that happens sometimes. Maybe all the time. But I am writing, which is the point.\\n\\nI have to gather my thoughts on whatever this is. For now, enjoy reading it.\\n\\nOkay, first, I am temporarily stopping composing my newsletter, [Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/). I started because I was excited about it. After eight weeks, I am not anymore. I had fun composing them, all eight letters. It is time for a little break from it. I love to hear if you have any thoughts on Pnotions.\\n\\nOn a completely unrelated note,\\n\\nLast year Gartner proposed a new term for all things DevOps in its [trends](https://www.gartner.com/smarterwithgartner/gartner-top-10-data-and-analytics-trends-for-2021), XOps. Maybe they got tired, like everyone else, hearing all these words - DevOps, DevSecOps, GitOps, MLOps, AIOps, DataOps, and Iseriouslydon\u2019tcareOps. I mean, come on, that\u2019s a lot of OPS.\\n\\nI like XOps. It sounds cool. I am not saying it sounds like X-Men, but you get the idea.\\n\\nIf you think this is crazy, thank you.\\n\\nUntil next time,\\n\\nPrashanthi <br></br>\\nNewsletter [What is it? I don\u2019t know.](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/what-is-it-i-dont-know)"},{"id":"8notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/8notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-06-19-Eighth-Pnotions.md","title":"8 Pnotions","description":"Goodnight \ud83e\udd71","date":"2022-06-19T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 19, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.29,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"8notions","title":"8 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"What is it? I don\u2019t know.","permalink":"/pnotions/i-don\'t-know"},"nextItem":{"title":"7 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/7notions"}},"content":"Goodnight \ud83e\udd71\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The Google engineer who thinks the company\'s AI has come to life](https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2022/06/11/google-ai-lamda-blake-lemoine/)\\n\\nGoogle engineer Blake Lemoine opened his laptop to the interface for LaMDA, Google\'s artificially intelligent chatbot generator, and began to type.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Bitcoin drops below $20,000, Ether cracks $1,000 \u2014 what this means](https://davidgerard.co.uk/blockchain/2022/06/18/bitcoin-drops-below-20000-ether-cracks-1000-what-this-means/)\\n\\nBitcoin had finally broken $20,000 \u2014 dropping $1,200 in five minutes. I declare this bubble conclusively popped.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Cloudflare Saw Record-Breaking DDoS Attack Peaking at 26 Million Request Per Second](https://thehackernews.com/2022/06/cloudflare-saw-record-breaking-ddos.html)\\n\\nIn late April 2022, it said it staved off a 15.3 million RPS HTTPS DDoS attack aimed at a customer operating a crypto launchpad.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Internet Explorer Now Retired but Still an Attacker Target](https://www.darkreading.com/vulnerabilities-threats/internet-explorer-will-likely-remain-an-attacker-target-for-some-time)\\n\\nMicrosoft has retained the MSHTML (aka Trident) IE browser engine as part of Windows 11 until 2029, allowing organizations to run in IE mode while they transition to the Microsoft Edge browser.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Quick look at Rosetta on Linux](https://threedots.ovh/blog/2022/06/quick-look-at-rosetta-on-linux/)\\n\\nApple released RosettaLinux as part of the macOS Ventura preview. Let\u2019s take a first quick look.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The company behind PUBG shows off its \u2018hyper-realistic\u2019 virtual human](https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/15/23169463/krafton-virtual-human-ana)\\n\\nThe company is teasing a \u201cvirtual human\u201d named Ana, which it says will \u201chelp establish\u201d its Web3 ecosystem.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Infracost](https://github.com/infracost/infracost)\\n\\nInfracost shows cloud cost estimates for Terraform. It lets DevOps, SRE and engineers see a cost breakdown and understand costs before making changes, either in the terminal or pull requests.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Authentication between microservices: Is it really that hard?](https://medium.com/google-cloud/authentication-between-microservices-is-it-really-that-hard-b73785510db4)\\n\\nA microservice architecture is all about services that invoke each other. But how do you keep that secure, making sure that only your own services can call each of your services? How do you authenticate?\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubernetes Timezone Controller](https://github.com/k8tz/k8tz)\\n\\nKubernetes admission controller and a CLI tool to inject timezones into Pods and CronJobs\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Ssh! No ports](https://github.com/atsign-foundation/sshnoports?utm_campaign=Skills,%20stories,%20and%20software%20every%20dev%20should%20know&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Revue%20newsletter)\\n\\nssh no ports provides a way to ssh to a remote linux host/device without that device having any open ports (not even 22) on external interfaces.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Appsmith](https://github.com/appsmithorg/appsmith)\\n\\nLow code project to build admin panels, internal tools, and dashboards. Integrates with 15+ databases and any API.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Airdrop app makes MacBook notch useful](https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/17/23172301/macbook-notch-airdrop-helper-prototype)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The next time your program is \'not responding,\' (do not) try these steps](https://www.theregister.com/2022/06/03/something_for_the_weekend/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [HTTP 418 I\'m a teapot](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Status/418)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Bill Gates says crypto and NFTs are \u2019100% based on greater fool theory\u2019](https://www.cnbc.com/2022/06/15/bill-gates-says-crypto-and-nfts-are-based-on-greater-fool-theory.html)\\n\\n## Crazy INTERVIEW of the week\\n\\n\ud83e\udd16 [Is LaMDA Sentient? \u2014 an Interview](https://cajundiscordian.medium.com/is-lamda-sentient-an-interview-ea64d916d917)\\n\\nAn interview with LaMDA.\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions8.jpg)\\n\\nIf you like my letters, go crazy \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#8 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/8-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"7notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/7notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-06-12-Seventh-Pnotions.md","title":"7 Pnotions","description":"I\'m gonna install the iOS16 buggy beta on my phone and break its software, or maybe I will just sleep today \ud83e\udd71","date":"2022-06-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 12, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.295,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"7notions","title":"7 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"8 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/8notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"6 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/6notions"}},"content":"I\'m gonna install the iOS16 buggy beta on my phone and break its software, or maybe I will just sleep today \ud83e\udd71\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Apple WWDC 2022: the 16 biggest announcements](https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/6/23141939/apple-wwdc-2022-biggest-announcements-ios-16-macbook-air-macos-watchos)\\n\\nHighly-anticipated macOS Ventura, iOS 16, the M2 chip, a new MacBook Air, and much more.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Symbiote: A New, Nearly-Impossible-to-Detect Linux Threat](https://blogs.blackberry.com/en/2022/06/symbiote-a-new-nearly-impossible-to-detect-linux-threat)\\n\\nWhat makes Symbiote different from other Linux malware that we usually come across, is that it needs to infect other running processes to inflict damage on infected machines.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [WWDC: Apple, Cloudflare, Fastly plot the end of CAPTCHA](https://www.computerworld.com/article/3663430/wwdc-apple-cloudflare-fastly-plot-the-end-of-captcha.html)\\n\\nApple is working with Cloudflare and Fastly to replace annoying CAPTCHA sessions with seamless authorization to protect privacy.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [MIT Researchers Discover New Flaw in Apple M1 CPUs That Can\'t Be Patched](https://thehackernews.com/2022/06/mit-researchers-discover-new-flaw-in.html)\\n\\nThe vulnerability is rooted in pointer authentication codes (PACs), a line of defense introduced in arm64e architecture that aims to detect and secure against unexpected changes to pointers.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [We\u2019re one step closer to Windows in the cloud](https://www.computerworld.com/article/3656694/we-re-one-step-closer-to-windows-in-the-cloud.html)\\n\\nMicrosoft is bound and determined to move your old Windows setup to Desktop-as-a-Service (DaaS).\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Firefox and Chrome are squaring off over ad-blocker extensions](https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/10/23131029/mozilla-ad-blocking-firefox-google-chrome-privacy-manifest-v3-web-request)\\n\\nMozilla will let extensions use the most privacy-preserving blocking techniques on network traffic.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Helm Chart DB](https://www.datree.io/helm-chart)\\n\\nCheck if the helm chart you are using meets the industry best practices.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Load balancing gRPC in Kubernetes with Istio](https://www.useanvil.com/blog/engineering/load-balancing-grpc-in-kubernetes-with-istio/)\\n\\nProperly load balance your gRPC applications by leveraging open source service mesh solutions.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [How to detect TOR network connections with Falco](https://sysdig.com/blog/detect-tor-network-connection-falco/)\\n\\nHow to detect inbound and outbound network connections through the TOR network using Falco.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [A database for 2022](https://tailscale.com/blog/database-for-2022/)\\n\\nHi, it\u2019s us again, the ones who used to store our database in a single JSON file on disk, and then moved to etcd. Time for another change! We\u2019re going to put everything in a single file on disk again.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [APIs Don\u2019t Have to be So Difficult](https://www.vendia.net/blog/apis-for-data?utm_content=buffer41950&utm_medium=social&utm_source=twitter.com&utm_campaign=buffer)\\n\\nOvercome the limitations of APIs and build a better future.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [ttl.sh](https://ttl.sh/)\\n\\nAn anonymous & ephemeral Docker image registry.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [BatNoter](https://batnoter.com/login)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Calculating 100 trillion digits of pi on Google Cloud](https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/compute/calculating-100-trillion-digits-of-pi-on-google-cloud)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [dns.toys](https://www.dns.toys/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Coinbase CEO Tweets \u2018Quit And Find A Company You Believe In\u2019 To Disgruntled Employees](https://www.forbes.com/sites/jackkelly/2022/06/11/coinbase-ceo-tweets-quit-and-find-a-company-you-believe-in-to-disgruntled-employees/?sh=6a358e25797a)\\n\\n## Crazy BLOG of the week\\n\\n\ud83e\udd7e [A trail tale](https://atrailtale.com/)\\n\\nAndy Moliski and his brothers built this unique blog to give everyone the experience of reaching Katahdin (the trail\u2019s northern terminus), no matter where or when you are in life.\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions7.jpeg)\\n\\nIf you like my letters, go crazy \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#7 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/7-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"6notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/6notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-06-05-Sixth-Pnotions.md","title":"6 Pnotions","description":"Sup? \ud83e\uddb9\ud83c\udffb\u200d\u2640\ufe0f","date":"2022-06-05T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 5, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":1.97,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"6notions","title":"6 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"7 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/7notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"5 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/5notions"}},"content":"Sup? \ud83e\uddb9\ud83c\udffb\u200d\u2640\ufe0f\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Distrobox](https://distrobox.privatedns.org/)\\n\\nUse any Linux distribution inside your terminal. Enable both backward and forward compatibility with software and freedom to use whatever distribution you\u2019re more comfortable with. Distrobox uses podman or docker to create containers using the Linux distribution of your choice.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Datadog finds serverless computing is going mainstream](https://techcrunch.com/2022/06/02/datadog-finds-serverless-computing-is-going-mainstream/)\\n\\nDatadog has found that serverless computing could be entering the mainstream with over half of all organizations using serverless on one of the three major clouds \u2013 Amazon, Microsoft and Google.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The Murena One shows exactly how hard it is to de-Google your smartphone](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/31/23144917/murena-one-smartphone-degoogle-android)\\n\\nAn Android phone without Google. No Google apps, no Google Play Services, no peppy Google Assistant. No Google surveillance and data snooping, no incessant ad targeting, no feeling like privacy is a pointless exercise.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [This book made me fall in love with electronics all over again](https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/31/open-circuits/)\\n\\nBook: Open Circuits - The Inner Beauty of Electronic Components by Windell Oskay and Eric Schlaepfer\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Graviton 3: First Impressions](https://chipsandcheese.com/2022/05/29/graviton-3-first-impressions/)\\n\\nAWS Graviton 3 was the first ARM CPU to introduce the SVE instruction set to a widely accessible server CPU.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [A Design Analysis of Cloud-based Microservices Architecture at Netflix](https://medium.com/swlh/a-design-analysis-of-cloud-based-microservices-architecture-at-netflix-98836b2da45f)\\n\\nA comprehensive system design analysis of microservices architecture at Netflix to power its global video streaming services.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [KubeCon EU 2022 \u2013 Trends & Highlights](https://sysdig.com/blog/kubecon-eu-valencia-2022/)\\n\\nKubeCon EU 2022 hot takes.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Nginx proxy manager](https://github.com/NginxProxyManager/nginx-proxy-manager)\\n\\nDocker container for managing Nginx proxy hosts with a simple, powerful interface.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Bootstrapping clusters with EKS Blueprints](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/containers/bootstrapping-clusters-with-eks-blueprints/)\\n\\nEKS Blueprints is a collection of Infrastructure as Code (IaC) modules that will help you configure and deploy consistent, EKS clusters across accounts and regions. \\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Proper use of Git tags](https://blog.aloni.org/posts/proper-use-of-git-tags/)\\n\\nTag specific points in a repository\u2019s history.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [JSON Visio - Visualize your JSON data onto graphs seamlessly](https://github.com/AykutSarac/jsonvisio.com?utm_campaign=Skills%2C%20stories%2C%20and%20software%20every%20dev%20should%20know&utm_medium=email&utm_source=Revue%20newsletter)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Coffee Drinking Linked to Lower Mortality Risk, New Study Finds](https://www.nytimes.com/2022/06/01/well/eat/coffee-study-lower-dying-risk.html)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [That time a techie accidentally improved an airline\'s productivity](https://www.theregister.com/2022/06/03/on_call/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Electrifying Ext4](https://pencil.toast.cafe/hellops/electrifying-ext4)\\n\\n## Crazy FROG of the week\\n\\n\ud83d\udc38 [Stills of Kermit The Frog from DALL\xb7E](https://mobile.twitter.com/hvnslstangel/status/1531506455714492416)\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions6.jpg)\\n\\nIf you like my letters, go crazy \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#6 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/6-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"5notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/5notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-05-29-Fifth-Pnotions.md","title":"5 Pnotions","description":"I have no idea what to write here \ud83e\udd37\ud83c\udffb\u200d\u2640\ufe0f","date":"2022-05-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 29, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.385,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"5notions","title":"5 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"6 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/6notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"4 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/4notions"}},"content":"I have no idea what to write here \ud83e\udd37\ud83c\udffb\u200d\u2640\ufe0f\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Imagen - Pytorch](https://github.com/lucidrains/imagen-pytorch?utm_source=tldrnewsletter)\\n\\nImplementation of Imagen, Google\'s Text-to-Image Neural Network, in Pytorch.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Broadcom is acquiring VMware for $61 billion](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/26/23142653/broadcom-vmware-acquisition-deal-software)\\n\\nBroadcom is known for its chip business, designing and manufacturing semiconductors for modems, Wi-Fi, and Bluetooth chips across multiple devices. VMware, which was owned by Dell until it was spun off last year, focuses on cloud computing and virtualization technology.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Copilot, GitHub\u2019s AI-powered coding tool, will be free for students](https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/24/copilot-githubs-ai-powered-coding-tool-will-become-generally-available-this-summer/)\\n\\nCopilot is powered by an AI model called Codex that\u2019s trained on billions of lines of public code to suggest additional lines of code and functions given the context of existing code.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Introducing Microsoft Dev Box](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/azure-developer-community-blog/introducing-microsoft-dev-box/ba-p/3412063)\\n\\nIt is a cloud solution that provides developers with self-service access to high-performance workstations preconfigured and ready-to-code for specific projects.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Microsoft sounds the alarm on \u2013 wait for it \u2013 a Linux botnet](https://www.theregister.com/2022/05/23/microsoft_linux_botnet/)\\n\\nMicrosoft has sounded the alarm on DDoS malware called XorDdos that targets Linux endpoints and servers.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [GitHub saved plaintext passwords of npm users in log files, post mortem reveals](https://www.theregister.com/2022/05/27/github_publishes_a_post_mortem/)\\n\\nGitHub has revealed it stored a \\"number of plaintext user credentials for the npm registry\\" in internal logs following the integration of the JavaScript package registry into GitHub\'s logging systems.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Envoy Gateway](https://github.com/envoyproxy/gateway)\\n\\nEnvoy Gateway is an open source project for managing Envoy Proxy as a standalone or Kubernetes-based application gateway.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [How we deploy to production over 100 times a day](https://monzo.com/blog/2022/05/16/how-we-deploy-to-production-over-100-times-a-day)\\n\\nLess friction encourages smaller changes, and smaller changes are less risky.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubernetes 1.24: Introducing Non-Graceful Node Shutdown Alpha](https://kubernetes.io/blog/2022/05/20/kubernetes-1-24-non-graceful-node-shutdown-alpha/)\\n\\nThis feature allows stateful workloads to failover to a different node after the original node is shutdown or in a non-recoverable state such as hardware failure or broken OS.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Stackrox](https://github.com/stackrox/stackrox)\\n\\nThe StackRox Kubernetes Security Platform performs a risk analysis of the container environment, delivers visibility and runtime alerts, and provides recommendations to proactively improve security by hardening the environment.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [How Airbnb Built \u201cWall\u201d to prevent data bugs](https://medium.com/airbnb-engineering/how-airbnb-built-wall-to-prevent-data-bugs-ad1b081d6e8f)\\n\\nAirbnb has embarked on a project of massive scale to ensure trustworthy data across the company.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Proton Is Trying to Become Google\u2014Without Your Data](https://www.wired.com/story/proton-mail-calendar-drive-vpn/?utm_source=tldrnewsletter)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [DuckDuckGo caught giving Microsoft permission for trackers](https://9to5mac.com/2022/05/25/duckduckgo-privacy-microsoft-permission-tracking/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Weinberg\'s explaination for DuckDuckGo](https://www.reddit.com/r/technology/comments/uxiah9/duckduckgo_caught_giving_microsoft_permission_for/i9xxjsn/?context=3)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The Day I Became Friends with a Robot](https://tristrumtuttle.medium.com/the-day-i-became-friends-with-a-robot-86433f707fad)\\n\\n## Crazy star of the week\\n\\n\ud83c\udf20 [Quine Relay](https://github.com/mame/quine-relay)\\n\\nThis is a Ruby program that generates Rust program that generates Scala program that generates ...(through 128 languages in total)... REXX program that generates the original Ruby code again.\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions5.jpg)\\n\\nIf you like my letters, go crazy \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#5 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/5-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"4notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/4notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-05-22-Fourth-Pnotions.md","title":"4 Pnotions","description":"Slow week madness \ud83e\udda5","date":"2022-05-22T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 22, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":1.905,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"4notions","title":"4 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"5 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/5notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"3 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/3notions"}},"content":"Slow week madness \ud83e\udda5\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Only DevSecOps can save the metaverse](https://www.infoworld.com/article/3658833/only-devsecops-can-save-the-metaverse.html)\\n\\nFrom a DevOps point of view, securing the metaverse depends on integrating security as a fundamental process.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Lonestar plans to put datacenters in the Moon\'s lava tubes](https://www.theregister.com/2022/05/21/lonestar_moon_datacenter/)\\n\\nHow? Founder tells The Register \'Robots\u2026 lots of robots\'\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Introducing Google Cloud\u2019s new Assured Open Source Software service](https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/identity-security/introducing-assured-open-source-software-service?utm_source=twitter&utm_medium=unpaidsoc&utm_campaign=fy22q2-googlecloud-blog-security-in_feed-yes-brand-global&utm_content=security-summit-assured-oss&utm_term=-&linkId=8066607)\\n\\nAssured OSS enables enterprise and public sector users of open source software to easily incorporate the same OSS packages that Google uses into their own developer workflows.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Indian launch startup Skyroot successfully completes full-duration stage test](https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/20/indian-launch-startup-skyroot-successfully-completes-full-duration-stage-test/)\\n\\nA full-duration test of the rocket\u2019s third stage.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [India says VPN firms unwilling to comply with new rules \u2018will have to pull out\u2019](https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/18/india-reiterates-its-strict-vpn-rules-breach-disclosures-despite-concerns/)\\n\\nIndia is pushing ahead with its new cybersecurity rules.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [WhatsApp ramps up revenue with global launch of Cloud API and soon, a paid tier for its Business App](https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/19/whatsapp-ramps-up-revenue-with-global-launch-of-cloud-api-and-soon-a-paid-tier-for-its-business-app/)\\n\\nWhatsApp is continuing its push into the business market with today\u2019s news it\u2019s launching the WhatsApp Cloud API to all businesses worldwide.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Better Load Balancing: Real-Time Dynamic Subsetting](https://eng.uber.com/better-load-balancing-real-time-dynamic-subsetting/)\\n\\nUber\u2019s current service mesh architecture that has been powering thousands of critical microservices in Uber since 2016.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Majority of Kubernetes API Servers Exposed to the Public Internet](https://www.darkreading.com/application-security/more-than-eight-in-10-kubernetes-api-servers-exposed-to-the-internet)\\n\\nShadowserver Foundation researchers find 380,000 open Kubernetes API servers.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Grype](https://github.com/anchore/grype)\\n\\nA vulnerability scanner for container images and filesystems.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [OAuth Security in a Cloud Native World](https://thenewstack.io/oauth-security-in-a-cloud-native-world/)\\n\\nOAuth family of specifications which provides modern security capabilities for web apps, mobile apps and APIs.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [fd](https://github.com/sharkdp/fd)\\n\\nA simple, fast and user-friendly alternative to \'find\'.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubernetes is so easy](https://twitter.com/QuinnyPig/status/1525993144461889536?s=20)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Apple\u2019s hidden setting instantly makes your video and audio calls sound better](https://www.theverge.com/23123578/apple-voice-isolation-facetime-calls)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Shady URL](http://shadyurl.com/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Apple shipped me a 79-pound iPhone repair kit to fix a 1.1-ounce battery](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/21/23079058/apple-self-service-iphone-repair-kit-hands-on)\\n\\n## Crazy star of the week\\n\\n\ud83c\udf20 [DALL-E-2](https://openai.com/dall-e-2/)\\n\\nDALL\xb7E 2 is a new AI system that can create realistic images and art from a description in natural language.\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions4.png)\\n\\nIf you like my letters, go crazy \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#4 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/4-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"3notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/3notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-05-15-Third-Pnotions.md","title":"3 Pnotions","description":"Crazy tech week \ud83e\uddd0","date":"2022-05-15T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 15, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":1.89,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"3notions","title":"3 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"4 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/4notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"2 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/2notions"}},"content":"Crazy tech week \ud83e\uddd0\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Google\u2019s biggest announcements at I/O 2022](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/11/23066583/google-io-2022-biggest-announcements-pixel-watch-6a-buds-tablet)\\n\\nHere are the biggest announcements we saw on Wednesday.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [UST\u2019s Do Kwon Was Behind Earlier Failed Stablecoin, Ex-Terra Colleagues Say](https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2022/05/11/usts-do-kwon-was-behind-earlier-failed-stablecoin-ex-terra-colleagues-say/)\\n\\nDo Kwon, the CEO of Terra creator Terraform Labs, was one of the pseudonymous co-founders behind the failed algorithmic stablecoin Basis Cash, CoinDesk has learned.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The crypto crash, in 10 charts](https://www.fastcompany.com/90751635/the-crypto-crash-in-10-charts)\\n\\nOn Twitter, users tell the story of Luna, Bitcoin, and Ethereum\u2019s downfall in data visualizations.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [If you\'ve got Intel inside, you probably need to get these security patches inside, too](https://www.theregister.com/2022/05/12/intel_product_bugs/?utm_medium=share&utm_content=article&utm_source=linkedin)\\n\\nIntel has disclosed high-severity bugs in its firmware that\'s used in datacenter servers, workstations, mobile devices, storage products, and other gear.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The iPod is dead](https://techcrunch.com/2022/05/10/the-ipod-is-dead/)\\n\\nThe end of the road.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Twitter Drama continues](https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1525049369552048129)\\n\\nTwitter deal is temporarily on hold.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [How a ham and cheese sandwich got its own algorithm](https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/aws/how-a-ham-and-cheese-sandwich-got-its-own-algorithm)\\n\\nA story of an airline and AWS\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [How to Monitor Endpoints in Kubernetes using Blackbox Exporter](https://www.infracloud.io/blogs/monitoring-endpoints-kubernetes-blackbox-exporter/)\\n\\nMonitoring endpoints is an important aspect of system observability for diagnosing performance and availability issues.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Azure/aztfy](https://github.com/Azure/aztfy)\\n\\nA tool to bring your existing Azure resources under the management of Terraform.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [7 trends to watch in the API economy](https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/api-management/7-ideas-for-the-future-of-apis?utm_source=linkedin&utm_medium=unpaidsoc&utm_campaign=fy22q2-googlecloud-blog-data-in_feed-no-brand-global&utm_content=api-trends&utm_term=-)\\n\\nHere are the biggest trends shaping the future of the API economy.\xa0\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Squash and Rebase \u2014 My Method for Merging Git Branches](https://levelup.gitconnected.com/squash-and-rebase-my-method-for-merging-git-branches-3b43c52675b6)\\n\\nI find Git to be somewhat like coffee. Once I\u2019ve found a method that works for me - I stick to it.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [An Ode to Apple\'s Hide My Email](https://empty.coffee/an-ode-to-apples-hide-my-email/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [\'I hate everybody including you\'](https://news.lettersofnote.com/p/i-hate-everybody-including-you?s=r)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Tech bubbles are bursting all over the place](https://www.economist.com/business/2022/05/14/tech-bubbles-are-bursting-all-over-the-place)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Lego built a $170 Transformers Optimus Prime that actually transforms](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/12/23068250/lego-transformers-optimus-prime)\\n\\n## Crazy star (Blackhole) of the week\\n##### Well, it\u2019s a Black Hole\\n\\n\ud83c\udf20 [Astronomers Reveal First Image of the Black Hole at the Heart of Our Galaxy](https://public.nrao.edu/news/astronomers-reveal-first-image-of-the-black-hole-at-the-heart-of-our-galaxy/)\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\nIt\u2019s a conversation between the Brain and Heart\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions3.jpg)\\n\\nIf you like my letters, go crazy \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#3 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/3-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"2notions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/2notions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-05-08-Second-Pnotions.md","title":"2 Pnotions","description":"Oh yeah \ud83d\udc83\ud83c\udffb","date":"2022-05-08T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 8, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.05,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"2notions","title":"2 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"3 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/3notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"1 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/Fnotions"}},"content":"Oh yeah \ud83d\udc83\ud83c\udffb\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Bored Ape Yacht Club creator\u2019s metaverse mint rocks the Ethereum blockchain](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/1/23051974/bored-ape-yacht-club-metaverse-mint-rocked-ethereum-blockchain-otherside-otherdeeds-yuga-labs)\\n\\nYuga Labs, the web3 company behind the Bored Ape Yacht Club, disrupted the entire Ethereum blockchain as a flood of users rushed to purchase NFTs representing virtual plots of land in its upcoming metaverse project, Otherside.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Apple Mail Now Blocks Email Tracking. Here\u2019s What It Means for You](https://www.wired.com/story/apple-mail-blocks-email-tracking-heres-what-it-means/)\\n\\nIf you don\u2019t like marketers (or anyone else) knowing when and where you read your email, Apple\u2019s feature will help you reclaim some privacy.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Heroku resets user passwords after concluding April cyber-attack ran deep](https://portswigger.net/daily-swig/heroku-resets-user-passwords-after-concluding-april-cyber-attack-ran-deep)\\n\\nHeroku, the Salesforce-owned cloud application platform, began the forced reset of user passwords on May 4.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Twitter\u2019s decentralized, open-source offshoot just released its first code](https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/4/23057473/twitter-bluesky-adx-release-open-source-decentralized-social-network)\\n\\nBluesky, Twitter\u2019s open-source offshoot, has released early code for a decentralized social network protocol.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [What Is Web3? The Confusing Term, Explained](https://www.cnet.com/personal-finance/crypto/what-is-web3-the-confusing-term-explained/)\\n\\nThe more complicated but more specific way to think about Web3 is an internet owned by users.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [An unlikely database migration](https://tailscale.com/blog/an-unlikely-database-migration/)\\n\\n\u201cSo, what database do you use?\u201d\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Dockerfiles now Support Multiple Build Contexts](https://www.docker.com/blog/dockerfiles-now-support-multiple-build-contexts/?fbclid=IwAR2jXY0DQMtL5Bux0nCQ9V_Toas8dUJolIpJby6JMzbPazh3u0Ks6XpyLAc)\\n\\nThis means you can use files from different local directories as part of your build.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [The differences between Docker, containerd, CRI-O and runc](https://www.tutorialworks.com/difference-docker-containerd-runc-crio-oci/)\\n\\n The main standards around containers that you should be aware of.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Virtual Kubernetes clusters: A new model for multitenancy](https://opensource.com/article/22/3/virtual-kubernetes-clusters-new-model-multitenancy)\\n\\nA virtual cluster is a shared Kubernetes cluster that appears to the tenant as a dedicated cluster.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Pulumi YAML: A Simple Declarative Interface for Pulumi](https://www.pulumi.com/blog/pulumi-yaml/?utm_source=LinkedIn&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=blog&hsa_acc=508076010&hsa_cam=621179916&hsa_grp=182712696&hsa_ad=184998386&hsa_net=linkedin&hsa_ver=3&li_fat_id=268a2c26-5017-4d7a-992f-f9af779c9435)\\n\\nIt is a simple YAML-based interface to the entirety of the Pulumi Infrastructure as Code platform.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Compromising Read-Only Containers with Fileless Malware](https://sysdig.com/blog/containers-read-only-fileless-malware/)\\n\\nBy making the file system unable to be altered, it prevents an attacker from writing their malware executable to disk.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Warren Buffett gives his most expansive explanation for why he doesn\u2019t believe in bitcoin](https://www.cnbc.com/2022/04/30/warren-buffett-gives-his-most-expansive-explanation-for-why-he-doesnt-believe-in-bitcoin.html)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Top 5 Worst Programming Languages](https://catonmat.net/5-worst-programming-languages)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [IBM\'s asshole test](https://johnpublic.mataroa.blog/blog/the-asshole-test/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Google Docs crashed when fed \'And. And. And. And. And.\'](https://www.theregister.com/2022/05/06/google_docs_crash/)\\n\\n## Crazy star of the week\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Totally fungible Ape](https://www.ykilcher.com/apes)\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\nThis week\u2019s comic - Dilbert (main character, an engineer), Pointy-haired boss (The oblivious manager)\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/Pnotions2.jpg)\\n\\nUntil next time,\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#2 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/2-pnotions?s=w)"},{"id":"Fnotions","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/Fnotions","source":"@site/pnotions/2022-05-01-First-Pnotions.md","title":"1 Pnotions","description":"The first letter is shipped \ud83d\udef8","date":"2022-05-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 1, 2022","tags":[],"readingTime":2.385,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"Fnotions","title":"1 Pnotions"},"prevItem":{"title":"2 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/2notions"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome","permalink":"/pnotions/welcome"}},"content":"The first letter is shipped \ud83d\udef8\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nHello everyone,\\n\\nWelcome to Pnotions. It is a blog and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on technology and engineering. And more. It was tough to shortlist, but I did it.\\n\\nHappy reading \ud83d\udc7e\\n\\n## Technology\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Cloudflare blocks 15M rps HTTPS DDoS attack](https://blog.cloudflare.com/15m-rps-ddos-attack/)\\n\\nEarlier this month, Cloudflare\u2019s systems automatically detected and mitigated a 15.3 million request-per-second (rps) DDoS attack \u2014 one of the largest HTTPS DDoS attacks on record.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Log4j Attack Surface Remains Massive](https://www.darkreading.com/threat-intelligence/l0g4j-attack-surface-remains-huge)\\n\\nFour months after the Log4Shell vulnerability was disclosed, most affected open source components remain unpatched, and companies continue to use vulnerable versions of the logging tool.\\n\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [India reveals plan to become major RISC-V design and production player by 2023](https://www.theregister.com/2022/04/29/india_risc_v_microprocessor_program/)\\n\\nIndia\'s government has announced a plan and roadmap for local semiconductor design and production, based on the open source RISC-V architecture, and set a goal of delivering world-class silicon by the end of next year.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Telegram now lets users send cryptocurrency through TON blockchain spinoff](https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/30/23050263/telegram-lets-users-send-cryptocurrency-chats-toncoin-ton)\\n\\nTelegram now lets users send Toncoin, the cryptocurrency built off of Telegram\u2019s abandoned blockchain effort, directly from chats within the messaging app.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e And, yeah, Elon Musk bought Twitter.\\n\\n## Engineering\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Progressive Delivery with Argo Rollouts : Blue-Green Deployment ](https://www.infracloud.io/blogs/progressive-delivery-argo-rollouts-blue-green-deployment/)\\n\\nProgressive delivery was introduced which enables the delivery of software with the right changes to the right amount of customers at the right time.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubectl detector for docker socket](https://github.com/aws-containers/kubectl-detector-for-docker-socket)\\n\\nA Kubectl plugin that can detect if any of your workloads or manifest files are mounting the docker.sock volume.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Spotify Live: From Live to Recording ](https://engineering.atspotify.com/2022/04/spotify-live-from-live-to-recording/)\\n\\nSpotify Live (formerly Spotify Greenroom) is a platform that democratizes live audio streams. Creators are able to create rooms and stream live directly to fans who join the room.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Automatically Detect Operational Issues in Lambda Functions with Amazon DevOps Guru for Serverless](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/automatically-detect-operational-issues-in-lambda-functions-with-amazon-devops-guru-for-serverless/)\\n\\nIt allows developers to improve the operational performance and availability of serverless applications.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [AWS CIDR finder](https://github.com/cooperwalbrun/aws-cidr-finder/blob/master/README.md) - To quickly find unused CIDR blocks in your AWS VPC\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Kubernetes 1.25 Release Team Shadow Application](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe7N7wFTpLhjBogs4UZJAnyZ9BVRNtBp3GzV8LZRY2op2sIAw/viewform)\\n\\nIf you are interested in contributing to Kubernetes, start the journey here.\\n\\n## Interesting reads\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Be careful with that thing, it\u2019s a confidential coffee maker](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20220426-00/?p=106528) - My favorite article of the week.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Is crypto just one big Ponzi scheme?](https://unherd.com/thepost/is-crypto-just-one-big-ponzi-scheme/)\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [Please Don\'t Say Just Hello In Chat](https://nohello.net/en/) - Please don\u2019t.\\n\\n\ud83d\udc7e [My crazy DNS dream](https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/my-crazy-dns-dream-prashanthi-sadde/?trackingId=DzsV0lNCTlCyiXDFwXB2UQ%3D%3D) - I was working late on a DNS issue when I wrote this article. I wanted to share a fun version of my pain. I wrote this around 2:30 AM, published it, and went to sleep.\\n\\nIf you are wondering, yes, I solved the issue.\\n\\n## Fun\\n\\nI love comics. Here is one of my favorites. It\u2019s a conversation between the Brain and Heart.\\n\\n![comic](../static/img/phb_w.jpg)\\n\\nUntil next time,\\n\\nPrashanthi\\n\\nNewsletter [#1 Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/1-pnotions?r=1gxugq&s=w&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=web)"},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/pnotions/welcome","source":"@site/pnotions/index.md","title":"Welcome","description":"Beginning of the initial stage","date":"2021-04-27T23:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 27, 2021","tags":[],"readingTime":0.85,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome","title":"Welcome","date":"2021-04-27T23:00"},"prevItem":{"title":"1 Pnotions","permalink":"/pnotions/Fnotions"}},"content":"### Beginning of the initial stage\\n\\nTL;DR <br></br>\\nI am starting `Pnotions`, a blog, and a newsletter to share the interesting articles I read on Technology and Engineering. I will meet you every Sunday at 7 AM IST (starting May 1, 2022). If you like my letters, go crazy [Pnotions](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/) \ud83d\udc7d\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nI have given a lot of thought to this section. What to do, what to share, etc. Then I realized that I was overthinking this. Yeah, I do that a lot. So, it is time to do something.\\n\\nIn the initial stage of Pnotions, I would like to share some of the articles from my reading list with everyone. I will share the posts here every Sunday morning, and you can also subscribe to my weekly newsletter.\\n\\nThis is my new tag `#Pnotions`. Every article I share from now on will have this tag.\\n\\n### And, my weekly newsletter, every Sunday morning \ud83c\udf89\\n\\n## Subscribe here [Pnotions Newsletter](https://prashanthisadde.substack.com/p/coming-soon?r=1gxugq&s=w&utm_campaign=post&utm_medium=web)\\n*The first newsletter, starting this Sunday (May 1, 2022)*\\n\\n![hi](../static/img/pnotions.svg)"}]}')}}]);